choices.text:
AbrahamBravo Ltd, CED Co., Francis Gingham and International Baddies Network are under investigation by HMRC and HM Treasury for money laundering.

The money laundering is believed to have been done through the tobacco trade, darkweb, tech start up, Costa Rica, shipping containers, medical equipment, disguise, hitman and Italian mafia.

KPMG is also said to be investigating the companies.

The money laundering is said to have been for the purpose of financing the operations of the companies.

The companies are said to be under investigation for their involvement in money laundering and other illegal activities.
